{"context": "Automotive giant AutoForge revealed its revolutionary solid-state battery, the PowerCell X, at an expo in Detroit last week. The new technology promises to triple the range of electric vehicles compared to current lithium-ion models. CTO Marcus Thorne showcased the battery by powering a prototype car for 1,200 miles on a single charge. Market experts expect the PowerCell X to be integrated into consumer vehicles by late 2025. This breakthrough represents the culmination of fifteen years of dedicated engineering research.", "question": "In which city was the PowerCell X battery revealed?", "answer": "Detroit"}
{"context": "A severe tremor measuring 7.2 on the Richter scale hit the northern province of Hokkaido, Japan, late last night, triggering widespread blackouts. Local authorities have confirmed at least 60 casualties, primarily due to building collapses in the old district. Prime Minister Fumio Kishida ordered the deployment of self-defense forces to accelerate rescue operations. Teams are currently digging through rubble to find four missing individuals in the village of Furano. Neighboring countries have pledged immediate assistance as damage assessments continue.", "question": "What is the total number of casualties confirmed so far?", "answer": "60"}
{"context": "The Los Angeles Lakers clinched a thrilling 105-103 win against the Boston Celtics in the NBA Finals showdown at the Crypto.com Arena. MVP LeBron James sank the decisive buzzer-beater with just two seconds remaining, electrifying the home crowd. Coach Darvin Ham commended the squad's determination after trailing by 15 points in the third quarter. More than 19,000 fans filled the arena, setting a new attendance record for the franchise. This victory secures the team's place in the history books as 18-time champions.", "question": "Which player made the game-winning shot for the Lakers?", "answer": "LeBron James"}
{"context": "Governor Robert Hayes declared his intention to run for the Senate seat in the upcoming mid-term elections during a town hall in Austin on Friday. His campaign prioritizes infrastructure modernization and healthcare accessibility for rural communities. This decision follows weeks of rumors about his challenge to the current seat holder. Hayes previously served as the Mayor of Houston for three terms before becoming Governor. Recent surveys indicate he has a slight advantage over his opponent in rural districts.", "question": "In which city did Governor Hayes announce his Senate run?", "answer": "Austin"}
{"context": "Renewable energy firm Solaris Tech launched a new series of carbon-negative panels constructed from recycled agricultural waste. The project, named 'Green Horizon,' targets the removal of 200 tons of atmospheric carbon by 2027. Unveiling ceremonies are planned concurrently in Berlin, Sydney, and São Paulo next month. For every panel installed, the company will donate $1.00 to reforestation projects globally. Climate activists have welcomed the initiative as a major stride toward net-zero emissions.", "question": "What is the title of the new environmental project?", "answer": "Green Horizon"}
{"context": "Catastrophic landslides in the Andean highlands have displaced approximately 8,500 villagers in Peru over the weekend. Unrelenting rainfall caused mountain slopes to give way, burying several small communities and farmlands. Officials have moved affected families to emergency camps in the capital city of Lima. Geologists warn that up to 40% of the region's potato harvest may be destroyed by the debris flows. Emergency rations consisting of dry goods, clean water, and tents are being transported by helicopter to isolated zones.", "question": "What is the number of villagers displaced by the landslides?", "answer": "8,500"}
{"context": "Drone delivery startup SkyRoute announced a milestone quarter with 200,000 successful packages delivered across North America. This growth was largely fueled by the launch of their heavy-lift Drone-Z model earlier this year. Founder Sarah Lin credited the achievement to improved battery life and relaxed aviation regulations in Canada. Their manufacturing hub in Toronto is now operating three shifts daily to fulfill pending orders. Rivals acknowledge SkyRoute's success in reducing delivery costs while maintaining safety standards.", "question": "How many packages did SkyRoute deliver in the recent quarter?", "answer": "200,000"}
{"context": "The International Atomic Energy Agency confirmed the safe decommissioning of the老旧 nuclear plant in Southern France on Thursday. Chief Inspector Pierre Dubois highlighted the complete containment of radioactive materials during the process. Decommissioning efforts in the region achieved 95% completion, leading to the site's reclassification. Although the plant is closed, radiation sensors will stay online to ensure long-term environmental safety. Energy ministers from 27 EU nations endorsed a new protocol for future plant closures.", "question": "Who highlighted the safe containment of materials during decommissioning?", "answer": "Pierre Dubois"}
{"context": "A sophisticated phishing campaign compromised the email servers of four major US healthcare providers early Monday morning. The incident disrupted appointment scheduling for thousands of patients in Texas, California, and New York. Cybersecurity experts at NetGuard traced the attack to a hacker collective calling themselves 'Silent Viper.' While no medical records were leaked, internal communication logs were temporarily locked by the malware. Hospitals are collaborating with the FBI to recover data and trace the origin of the breach.", "question": "What is the alias of the hacker group behind the phishing campaign?", "answer": "Silent Viper"}
{"context": "SpaceX successfully deployed the Starlink Gen-2 satellite cluster from Vandenberg Base, California, marking a new era in global internet connectivity. Astronauts Elena Rossi and Kenji Tanaka monitored the deployment from the Dragon capsule during a four-day orbital mission. The project aims to provide high-speed internet to remote regions worldwide by 2026. Hundreds of onlookers watched the sunset launch from the nearby beaches. This mission signifies the peak of five years of rapid development in low-earth orbit technology.", "question": "From which location was the Starlink Gen-2 cluster deployed?", "answer": "Vandenberg Base, California"}
{"context": "The municipality of Seattle passed a contentious traffic regulation that reduces speed limits in residential zones to 20 mph. Councilmember Janet Lee argued the change is vital to reduce pedestrian accidents and improve neighborhood safety. Critics intend to challenge the rule in court, alleging it infringes on drivers' rights and increases commute times. The new speed limit will be enforced starting March 15th, following a public awareness campaign. Safety organizations have hailed the move as a crucial step toward vision zero goals.", "question": "On what date will the new traffic regulation be enforced?", "answer": "March 15th"}
{"context": "Golfer Rory McIlroy won the Masters Tournament in a playoff against Scottie Scheffler at Augusta National. The final round extended into extra holes, concluding with a birdie on the 18th green. McIlroy completes the career grand slam, joining an elite group of golfers who have won all four majors. The winner's purse was awarded at $3.6 million, the highest in tournament history. Spectators at the clubhouse cheered loudly as the trophy was presented under the twilight sky.", "question": "How did the Masters Tournament conclude for Rory McIlroy?", "answer": "in a playoff"}
{"context": "An unprecedented heatwave swept across the Iberian Peninsula, pushing temperatures to 47 degrees Celsius and shutting down major highways for two days. Prime Minister Pedro Sánchez mobilized emergency water tankers to assist dehydrated travelers in the Andalusia region. Thermometers soared to record highs, creating hazardous conditions for outdoor workers and the elderly. Local vineyards reported significant grape loss due to the scorching sun, though tourism numbers remained high as visitors sought indoor activities. Utility teams are scrambling to repair power grids overloaded by air conditioning usage in 25,000 households.", "question": "What maximum temperature did the heatwave reach?", "answer": "47 degrees Celsius"}
{"context": "Biotech firm GeneCure obtained emergency authorization from the EMA for its groundbreaking gene therapy, CellRepair. Trials demonstrated a 65% recovery rate in patients suffering from rare blood disorders. The therapy will be administered in specialized clinics across Europe beginning next quarter at a price of €1.8 million per treatment. Dr. Hans Weber, the project lead, described the authorization as a 'monumental leap for genetic medicine.' Payers are currently analyzing cost-effectiveness to establish reimbursement guidelines for patients.", "question": "What recovery rate did CellRepair demonstrate in clinical trials?", "answer": "65%"}
{"context": "The ASEAN summit wrapped up in Bangkok with participating countries ratifying a landmark pact on digital trade harmonization. Ministers agreed to streamline cross-border data flows and reduce digital tariffs by 40% by 2030. Thai Prime Minister Srettha Thavisin chaired the summit, stressing the importance of inclusive digital growth for smaller nations. The treaty outlines specific roadmaps for adopting unified cybersecurity standards and e-payment systems. Tech industry leaders expressed hope but noted that implementation timelines vary significantly between members.", "question": "By what year do ASEAN nations aim to reduce digital tariffs by 40%?", "answer": "2030"}
{"context": "A collision between two passenger ferries occurred in the busy harbor of Istanbul, Turkey, on Sunday afternoon. Roughly 150 passengers were on board the vessels, leading to a rapid evacuation of those near the impact zone. Coast guard units created a safety perimeter to prevent fuel leaks from contaminating the Bosphorus strait. The Maritime Safety Authority has launched an inquiry to determine if navigational errors caused the incident. Nearby schools and businesses were advised to stay indoors briefly while rescue boats operated.", "question": "How many passengers were aboard the ferries during the collision?", "answer": "150"}
{"context": "Gaming conglomerate PlayZone revealed plans to acquire studio DreamCraft in a transaction worth $12 billion. The merged company would command over 20% of the global mobile gaming sector, prompting scrutiny from competition watchdogs. PlayZone CEO Alice Wong claimed the acquisition would boost innovation in virtual reality experiences. Users of both platforms will see no changes to their accounts during the planned 12-month transition. Rival studios like GameHub and CorePlay experienced a dip in share value after the announcement.", "question": "What is the financial value of the PlayZone and DreamCraft acquisition?", "answer": "$12 billion"}
{"context": "Torrential rains in the Amazon basin have submerged more than 80,000 hectares of rainforest in Brazil this month. Swollen rivers overflowed their banks, isolating indigenous communities and threatening biodiversity hotspots. Rescue teams from five South American nations joined local efforts to deliver supplies by boat. The historic trading posts near Manaus are at risk of flooding, causing concern among historians and ecologists. Officials fear that illegal logging activities may have exacerbated the severity of the runoff.", "question": "How many hectares of rainforest have been submerged by the rains?", "answer": "80,000"}
{"context": "The Bank of England declared a half-percent increase in the base rate to tackle inflation persisting above 4%. Governor Andrew Bailey suggested that additional hikes could occur if wage growth remains unchecked. Home loan rates swiftly rose to 6.8%, putting pressure on the property market's stability. Analysts forecast this action will dampen retail activity but strengthen the pound against the euro. The subsequent monetary policy committee meeting is set for early October to evaluate economic indicators.", "question": "To what percentage did home loan rates rise following the announcement?", "answer": "6.8%"}
{"context": "Renowned poet Ocean Vuong published his new collection of essays 'Time is a Mother' this morning. The work delves into themes of grief and memory through the perspective of a Vietnamese-American immigrant. Initial pre-sale figures surpassed 150,000 units, establishing it as the top-selling non-fiction release of the season. Vuong is scheduled for a reading tour beginning in Hanoi before stopping in San Francisco and Paris. Literary reviewers have already nominated the collection for the National Book Award.", "question": "How many units did 'Time is a Mother' sell in pre-sales initially?", "answer": "150,000"}
